HEADWORD: Pinkster
<hw>Pink"ster</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>pinkster</ets>, <ets>pinksteren</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/. See
<er>Pentecost</er>.]</ety> <def>Whitsuntide.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pingster</asp> and <asp>pinxter</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pinkster flower</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the rosy
flower of the <spn>Azalea nudiflora</spn>; also, the shrub itself; --
called also <altname>Pinxter blomachee</altname> by the New York
descendants of the Dutch settlers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pink stern</ent>⟦br⟧
